    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim the green stalk off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-plant-based-gochujang-veggie-stew-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped aubergine</strong> and <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-plant-based-gochujang-veggie-stew-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once lightly browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>gochujang paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan</p><p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-plant-based-gochujang-veggie-stew-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>single soy </strong>and <strong>soy sauce </strong>to the pan and mix it all together</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook, covered, for a further 12-15 min or until the butternut squash is tender and the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-plant-based-gochujang-veggie-stew-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-plant-based-gochujang-veggie-stew-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Cut the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-plant-based-gochujang-veggie-stew-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the butternut squash has softened, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>green beans</strong> and <strong>miso </strong>to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook, covered for a further 3-4 min or until the green beans are tender</p><p>Once tender, add the juice of half your <strong>lime[s]</strong> and the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> to the pan and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy plant-based gochujang veggie stew</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-plant-based-gochujang-veggie-stew-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy plant-based gochujang veggie stew </strong>in bowls over the <strong>cooked cauliflower rice</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>chopped spring onion</strong></p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
